items.name: Arched back female orgasm LoCon
items.description:
Arched back female orgasm LoCon

LoRA request queue on my discord: https://discord.gg/DAfjhRfyEM

This model was trained using ~40 images of characters in the pose. It was trained on the NAI model so it should work with most anime based models. The main concept that got trained was a woman on the back with an arched back while ejaculating. Some additional prompting is required, like hand positions (might require another LoRA at a lower weight depending on what you want) and expressions. It was a mix of fingering, sex toys and hands somewhere else. It isn't perfect but if you know a thing or two about SD tools (inpaint, open pose etc.) you can get some nice images.

Recommended weight is between 0.7 and 1.

The triggerword is arched back orgasm

Example images were generated using anyhentai with 30 steps, then hires. fixed by 1.5 with adetailer enabled for the faces

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

items.name: Squirrel Girl (Doreen Green, Marvel Comics)
items.description:
Squirrel Girl (Marvel) LyCORIS!

Making models can be time consuming and expensive. If you like what I do consider giving this a rating and commissioning a model or buying me a borgar🍔!

One of the most surprisingly powerful Marvel characters out there! (She even took down thanos on her own?) Brought to you as a LyCORIS.

Some things to note: this is her typical marvel comics debut outfit and sometimes the tail is hit or miss. Given its a large tail, and her similar hair color, its amazing the tail doesnt always get absorbed into her hair!

The trigger word for this Locon is sgv1 and replicates her main outfit easily without additional prompting. Strength of 1.0-1.1 works the best. Sometimes will have to specify brown eyes, squirrel tail. You can also get her squirrel friend(s) to appear with the animal, squirrel tags, but this is much more random.

As always join my discord server and boost if you want to take part in votes on my next model creations. Thanks!

items.name: FoolKat GOD-OF-SHADE
items.description:
This is the twenty-first model in my GOD-OF series. This will most likely be the last of the GOD-OF series. I am still working on getting a SDXL anime model created and I have a few of the GODDESS series models ready to upload soon. The GODDESS series won't have anywhere near as many models as this one did. It will probably have 3-5 models total.

You can find all the models at GOD-OF-GREED, GOD-OF-ENVY, GOD-OF-LOVE, GOD-OF-ANIME, GOD-OF-LUST, GOD-OF-JUSTICE, GOD-OF-TIME, GOD-OF-FANTASY, GOD-OF-JOY, GOD-OF-HORROR, GOD-OF-PRIDE, GOD-OF-PUNK, GOD-OF-STORMS, GOD-OF-EUPHORIA, GOD-OF-GLUTTONY, GOD-OF-THE-WEST, GOD-OF-BEAUTY, GOD-OF-SEDUCTION, GOD-OF-MONOCHROME, and GOD-OF-PEACE.

This model was created when attempting to create version 3 of GOD-OF-MONOCHROME. As such, it does occasionally make monochromatic images. However, it primarily makes images with an art style that reminds me of cel shading in old 2D animation.

The model has Blessed2 VAE baked into it, so no VAE required.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

items.name: Nefuren Ruku Insania/ネフレン・ルク・インサニア (Shuumatsu Nani Shitemasu ka? Isogashii desu ka?)
items.description:
• THIS MODEL HAS TWO FILES. YOU NEED TO USE THEM TOGETHER!!!
  • The associated trigger words are only for reference, it may need to be adjusted at some times.
  • The recommended weight for the embedding model is 1, which provides higher fidelity; if greater generalization is required, it can be lowered to 0.5.
  • The recommended weight for the LoRA model is 0.85; if there's evidence of contamination, consider lowering it to 0.6.

How to Use This Model

THIS MODEL HAS TWO FILES. YOU NEED TO USE THEM TOGETHER!!!. In this case, you need to download both nephren_sukasuka.pt and nephren_sukasuka.safetensors, then use nephren_sukasuka.pt as texture inversion embedding, and use nephren_sukasuka.safetensors as LoRA at the same time.

このモデルには2つのファイルがあります。一緒に使う必要があります！！！。 この場合、nephren_sukasuka.ptとnephren_sukasuka.safetensorsの両方をダウンロード する必要があります。nephren_sukasuka.ptをテクスチャ反転埋め込みとして使用し、同時にnephren_sukasuka.safetensorsをLoRAとして使用してください。

这个模型有两个文件。你需要同时使用它们！！！。 在这种情况下，您需要下载nephren_sukasuka.pt和nephren_sukasuka.safetensors这两个文件，然后将nephren_sukasuka.pt用作纹理反转嵌入， 同时使用nephren_sukasuka.safetensors作为LoRA。

이 모델은 두 개의 파일이 있습니다. 두 파일을 함께 사용해야 합니다!!!. 이 경우에는 nephren_sukasuka.pt와 nephren_sukasuka.safetensors 두 파일을 모두 다운로드하신 다음에 nephren_sukasuka.pt을 텍스처 반전 임베딩으로 사용하고, 동시에 nephren_sukasuka.safetensors을 LoRA로 사용하셔야 합니다.

(Translated with ChatGPT)

The trigger word is nephren_sukasuka, and the recommended tags are best quality, masterpiece, highres, solo, {nephren_sukasuka:1.15}, twintails, grey_eyes, ribbon, hair_ribbon, closed_mouth, upper_body.

How This Model Is Trained

This model is trained with HCP-Diffusion. And the auto-training framework is maintained by DeepGHS Team.

Why Some Preview Images Not Look Like Nephren Sukasuka

All the prompt texts used on the preview images (which can be viewed by clicking on the images) are automatically generated using clustering algorithms based on feature information extracted from the training dataset. The seed used during image generation is also randomly generated, and the images have not undergone any selection or modification. As a result, there is a possibility of the mentioned issues occurring.

In practice, based on our internal testing, most models that experience such issues perform better in actual usage than what is seen in the preview images. The only thing you may need to do is adjusting the tags you are using.

I Felt This Model May Be Overfitting or Underfitting, What Shall I Do

Our model has been published on huggingface repository - CyberHarem/nephren_sukasuka, where models of all the steps are saved. Also, we published the training dataset on huggingface dataset - CyberHarem/nephren_sukasuka, which may be helpful to you.

Why Not Just Using The Better-Selected Images

Our model's entire process, from data crawling, training, to generating preview images and publishing, is 100% automated without any human intervention. It's an interesting experiment conducted by our team, and for this purpose, we have developed a complete set of software infrastructure, including data filtering, automatic training, and automated publishing. Therefore, if possible, we would appreciate more feedback or suggestions as they are highly valuable to us.

Why Can't the Desired Character Outfits Be Accurately Generated

Our current training data is sourced from various image websites, and for a fully automated pipeline, it's challenging to accurately predict which official images a character possesses. Consequently, outfit generation relies on clustering based on labels from the training dataset in an attempt to achieve the best possible recreation. We will continue to address this issue and attempt optimization, but it remains a challenge that cannot be completely resolved. The accuracy of outfit recreation is also unlikely to match the level achieved by manually trained models.

In fact, this model's greatest strengths lie in recreating the inherent characteristics of the characters themselves and its relatively strong generalization capabilities, owing to its larger dataset. As such, this model is well-suited for tasks such as changing outfits, posing characters, and, of course, generating NSFW images of characters!😉".

For the following groups, it is not recommended to use this model and we express regret:

  1. Individuals who cannot tolerate any deviations from the original character design, even in the slightest detail.
  2. Individuals who are facing the application scenarios with high demands for accuracy in recreating character outfits.
  3. Individuals who cannot accept the potential randomness in AI-generated images based on the Stable Diffusion algorithm.
  4. Individuals who are not comfortable with the fully automated process of training character models using LoRA, or those who believe that training character models must be done purely through manual operations to avoid disrespecting the characters.
  5. Individuals who finds the generated image content offensive to their values.
